# L2TPv2 wire decode: truncated input is rejected
# VALIDATES: AC-22 -- `ze l2tp decode` exits non-zero and reports a parse error
#            when the hex blob is too short for the claimed header layout.
# PREVENTS: silent success on malformed wire input.
stdin=payload:hex=c8
cmd=foreground:seq=1:exec=ze l2tp decode:stdin=payload
expect=exit:code=1
expect=stderr:contains=short buffer
